summary: An ordinance accepting deeds from S. R. Weller and Ida J. Weller, his wife; M. E. Kilbourne, a single woman; Ellen Jane Wylde and George F. Folsom; Frank D. Plumb and Lena A. Plumb his wife; Theodore N. Haller, Charlotte Haller McKee, George Dorffel and Otilda Dorffel, his wife; Olson Land Company; Angus W. Cassels and Elizabeth B. Cassels, his wife; Samuel Friedlander and Augusta Friedlander, his wife; Arthur G. Seymour and Margaret L. Seymour, his wife and Harold Seymour and Grace A. Seymour, his wife; West Seattle Land & Improvement Company; M. M. Lyter and Magdalene F. Lyter, husband and wife; C. C. Buckley and Hanora K. Buckley, his wife; William H. King, Executor, James E. King, Executor, Julia A. King Cunningham, Executrix, respectively of the estate of Thomas J. King, Deceased; The Marine National Bank; Bertha Winge, a widow, for the purpose of establishing Marine Drive.
